Dreams will not come true unless you have worked hard to be ready for the challenges ahead. During the talk, Dr. Van Pham from Salem State University, Massachusetts, USA will be talking about how to prepare yourself for the best educational experience abroad. Dr. Pham will share her insights from Vietnamese as well as American perspectives. Open to the public (students and parents are both welcome.)

Speaker: Dr. Van Pham is an associate professor of economics at Salem State University in Massachusetts, United States of America. She is currently a Fulbright Scholar at Fulbright Economics Teaching Program in Ho Chi Minh City. She was a student and a university lecturer in Vietnam before coming to the US to do her graduate studies and then teaching at university level.